+# Live Migrate Azure Cosmos DB SQL API Containers data with Spark Connector and Azure Databricks
+
+This sample shows how to live migrate between Azure Cosmos DB SQL API containers using the [Azure Cosmos DB Spark Connector](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/cosmos-db/sql/create-sql-api-spark). 
+
+# Setup Azure Databricks
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+* [Provision an Azure Databricks cluster](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/databricks/scenarios/quickstart-create-databricks-workspace-portal?tabs=azure-portal).
+
+* Ensure it has network access to your source and target Azure Cosmos DB Containers.
+
+
+## Provision a Spark cluster
+
+Select the latest Azure Databricks runtime version which supports Spark 3.0 or higher.
+
+![image](./media/spark-cluster.jpg)
+
+## Install Azure Cosmos DB Spark Connector jar
+

+# Live Migrate Azure Cosmos DB SQL API Containers data with Spark Connector and Azure Databricks
+
+This sample shows how to live migrate between Azure Cosmos DB SQL API containers using the [Azure Cosmos DB Spark Connector](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/cosmos-db/sql/create-sql-api-spark). 
+
+# Setup Azure Databricks
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+* [Provision an Azure Databricks cluster](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/databricks/scenarios/quickstart-create-databricks-workspace-portal?tabs=azure-portal).
+
+* Ensure it has network access to your source and target Azure Cosmos DB Containers.
+
+
+## Provision a Spark cluster
+
+Select the latest Azure Databricks runtime version which supports Spark 3.0 or higher.
+
+![image](./media/spark-cluster.jpg)
+
+## Install Azure Cosmos DB Spark Connector jar
+
+* Install the Azure Cosmos DB Spark Connector jar on the cluster by providing maven co-ordinates `com.azure.cosmos.spark:azure-cosmos-spark_3-2_2-12:4.7.0`:', 'path': +# Live Migrate Azure Cosmos DB SQL API Containers data with Spark Connector and Azure Databricks
+
+This sample shows how to live migrate between Azure Cosmos DB SQL API containers using the [Azure Cosmos DB Spark Connector](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/cosmos-db/sql/create-sql-api-spark). 
+
+# Setup Azure Databricks
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+* [Provision an Azure Databricks cluster](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/databricks/scenarios/quickstart-create-databricks-workspace-portal?tabs=azure-portal).
+
+* Ensure it has network access to your source and target Azure Cosmos DB Containers.
+
+
+## Provision a Spark cluster
+
+Select the latest Azure Databricks runtime version which supports Spark 3.0 or higher.
+
+![image](./media/spark-cluster.jpg)
+
+## Install Azure Cosmos DB Spark Connector jar
+
+* Install the Azure Cosmos DB Spark Connector jar on the cluster by providing maven co-ordinates `com.azure.cosmos.spark:azure-cosmos-spark_3-2_2-12:4.7.0`:', 'path': 'sdk/cosmos/azure-cosmos-spark_3_2-12/Samples/DatabricksLiveContainerMigration/README.md', 'position': 22, 'original_position': 22, 'commit_id': '69f46b85473379b5b0107c3ebecf273b721c3254', 'original_commit_id': '69f46b85473379b5b0107c3ebecf273b721c3254', 'user': {'login': 'TheovanKraay', 'id': 24420698, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjI0NDIwNjk4', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/24420698?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/TheovanKraay', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/TheovanKraay/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, 'body': "Doesn't that also run the risk of latest jar containing some code that is not backwards compatible with the sample code at the time user installs it? 'updated_at': '2022-04-05T20:47:58Z', 'closed_at': None, 'author_association': 'NONE', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': '
I'm trying to understand what is meant by the note in this documentation:

**"The  Azure Cosmos DB Java V4 SDK comes with the bulk executor library built-in to the SDK. [...] Azure Cosmos DB Java V4 SDK is the current recommended solution for Java bulk support."**

However there is no explanation of what this means in practice.  The code samples here don't work with V4 but if you go to the API docs for V4 of the SDK, there is no mention of bulk support or how it's implemented. Also, the V4 migration guide (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/sql/migrate-java-v4-sdk?tabs=java-v4-async) doesn't mention bulk support or how people using the older bulk executor library should migrate. There IS a link in that migration document referencing bulk operations - but it links back to this document which talks about needing to migrate to V4.

Could we update the migration docs to reference what people who are using the older bulk executor library need to do to take advantage of the "built in" support in v4?

I'm trying to understand what is meant by the note in this documentation:

**"The  Azure Cosmos DB Java V4 SDK comes with the bulk executor library built-in to the SDK. [...] Azure Cosmos DB Java V4 SDK is the current recommended solution for Java bulk support."**

However there is no explanation of what this means in practice.  The code samples here don't work with V4 but if you go to the API docs for V4 of the SDK, there is no mention of bulk support or how it's implemented. Also, the V4 migration guide (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/sql/migrate-java-v4-sdk?tabs=java-v4-async) doesn't mention bulk support or how people using the older bulk executor library should migrate. There IS a link in that migration document referencing bulk operations - but it links back to this document which talks about needing to migrate to V4.

Could we update the migration docs to reference what people who are using the older bulk executor library need to do to take advantage of the "built in" support in v4?

 Azure Managed Instance for Apache Cassandra provides automated deployment and scaling operations for managed open-source Apache Cassandra data centers. This article defines the management operations and features provided by the service. It also explains the separation of responsibilities between the Azure support team and customers when maintaining standalone and [hybrid](configure-hybrid-cluster.md) clusters.
 
+## Compaction
+* The system currently does not perform a major compaction. 
+* Repair (see below) performs a Merkle tree compaction, which is a special kind of compaction.
+* Deoending on the compaction startegy on the keyspace Cassandra will automaticlaly compact when the keyspace reaches a certain size. We recommend to carefully select a compaction strategy for your workload and not perform any manual compactions outside.', 'path':  Azure Managed Instance for Apache Cassandra provides automated deployment and scaling operations for managed open-source Apache Cassandra data centers. This article defines the management operations and features provided by the service. It also explains the separation of responsibilities between the Azure support team and customers when maintaining standalone and [hybrid](configure-hybrid-cluster.md) clusters.
 
+## Compaction
+* The system currently does not perform a major compaction. 
+* Repair (see below) performs a Merkle tree compaction, which is a special kind of compaction.
+* Deoending on the compaction startegy on the keyspace Cassandra will automaticlaly compact when the keyspace reaches a certain size.
